author: COMSOL
description: A rotor with permanent magnets and a nonlinear magnetic material is rotating within a stator of the same magnetic material. The generated voltage in windings around the stator is calculated as a function of time. COMSOL Multiphysics models the rotation with assemblies and identity pairs, using a prescribed rotation coordinate transform in Moving Mesh. The nonlinearity of the magnetic material is modeled using an interpolating function defined in a material library.

settings.value:
Internal Rotor – Surface Mounted Magnets

This is an internal rotor part with surface mounted permanent magnets. It is developed primarily to be used together with an external stator part, in order to simulate rotating electric motors.

For more information, check the documentation in the corresponding *.pdf document.

settings.name: commentsinfile
settings.value:
External Stator – Slotted

This is an external slotted stator part. It is developed primarily to be used together with an internal rotor part, in order to simulate rotating electric motors.

For more information, check the documentation in the corresponding *.pdf document.
